metadata.name: Walking Sideways
metadata.description:
Vibrancy, colour, decadence and joy. I never felt any of these for the most part of my childhood.

I was constantly being reminded that there was so much colour and beauty in the world that surrounds me.

My eye however, couldn't see past the gloam and murk that I was made to feel. And these were painted in eerie shades of black. 

I was expected to set myself on a path of linearity, instead, I found myself walking sideways.
